Lex Kim Book Reports site

=In order to run this app, you must have the following installed and available at the command line:

1. Java
2. pdf2swf - via http://www.swftools.org/, also avaialable via apt-get in Debian/Ubuntu
3. ODF converter - via http://www.oooninja.com/2008/01/convert-openxml-docx-etc-in-linux-using.html and
  http://www.oooninja.com/2008/01/openxml-translator-odf-converter-11.html
  Run:

     sudo ln -s /usr/lib/libtiff.so.4 /usr/lib/libtiff.so.3

  For this to work I also had to create a link:

    sudo ln -s /usr/lib/libtiff.so.4 /usr/lib/libtiff.so.3

For JodConverter to work, must have the openoffice daemon running, using xvfb ( sudo aptitude install xvfb) with command like:
  sudo nohup  xvfb-run -a soffice -headless -accept="socket,port=8100;urp;"
Also make sure package openoffice.org is install on Debian machine
